      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you do this, there\u0027s no reason to use RWLock, it protect tiny portion of the code. I was suggesting to use RWLock to make sure we never create duplicate clients:\n\n  cc.lock.RLock()\n  client, ok :\u003d cc.clients[instance]\n  cc.lock.RUnlock()\n\n  if ok {\n    return client\n  }\n\n  cc.lock.Lock()\n  defer cc.lock.Unlock()\n\n  client, ok :\u003d cc.clients[instance]\n  if ok {\n    return client // someone actually created the client already\n  }\n\n  client :\u003d ...\n  cc.clients[instances] \u003d client\n  return client",
